    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Shock Waves From the Mideast, on Two Fronts</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Keith Jones letter says terrorist bombing of USS Cole in Yemen illustrates campaign issue on US military, which he charges has been reduced to dangerously low levels (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The apparent terrorist action against the American Navy destroyer Cole (''Blast Kills Sailors on U.S. Ship in Yemen,'' front page, Oct. 13) illustrates a critical campaign issue: our military has been reduced to dangerously low levels under the Clinton-Gore administration.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The apparent terrorist action against the American Navy destroyer Cole (''Blast Kills Sailors on U.S. Ship in Yemen,'' front page, Oct. 13) illustrates a critical campaign issue: our military has been reduced to dangerously low levels under the Clinton-Gore administration.</p>
        <p>As a former military officer, I asked myself why our warships would refuel in a dangerous foreign port rather than safely on the high seas. This country can afford refueling ships to keep our sailors out of potential danger.</p>
        <p>In the debate, Al Gore said our military must remain strong enough for the job. Let's see him try that one on the grieving families of those sailors who died for lack of adequate financing.</p>
        <p>KEITH JONES  Lexington, Ky., Oct. 13, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
